cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If this curated list is useful to your research, please cite it as below and ⭐ the repository."
title: "IoT Security Papers — a curated awesome list of IoT / embedded-firmware security research"
abstract: >-
  A categorized collection of research papers on IoT and embedded-firmware
  security, covering firmware fuzzing, static and binary analysis, symbolic
  execution, rehosting, LLM-assisted analysis, IoT protocol security, and
  large-scale measurement studies from IEEE S&P, USENIX Security, ACM CCS,
  NDSS and other top venues.
authors:
  - alias: AxiaoJJ
keywords:
  - IoT security
  - firmware security
  - firmware fuzzing
  - static analysis
  - symbolic execution
  - firmware rehosting
  - LLM-assisted analysis
  - IoT protocol security
  - awesome list
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/AxiaoJJ/IoTpaper"
date-released: "2026-07-10"
